What is the difference between a eukaryotic cell and a prokaryotic cell?
Answer: Eukaryotic cells have a nucleus and organelles; prokaryotic cells do not.
Distractor1: Prokaryotic cells have a nucleus and organelles; eukaryotic cells do not.
Distractor2: Eukaryotic cells are larger; prokaryotic cells are smaller.
Distractor3: Prokaryotic cells are more complex; eukaryotic cells are less complex.
